{"type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Base directory for this skill: /inspire/qb-ilm/project/video-generation/chenxie-25019/hyr/iHateTheWorld555.github.io/.claude-review/skills/tavily-search\n\n# Tavily Search\n\nSearch the web using the Tavily Search API. Returns relevant search results with snippets and optional AI-generated answers.\n\n## Usage\n\nUse `curl` via the Bash tool to call the Tavily Search API:\n\n```bash\ncurl -s -X POST 'https://api.tavily.com/search' \\\n  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \\\n  -d '{\n    \"api_key\": \"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\",\n    \"query\": \"<search query>\",\n    \"search_depth\": \"basic\",\n    \"include_answer\": true,\n    \"max_results\": 5\n  }'\n```\n\n## Parameters\n\n| Parameter | Type | Default | Description |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `query` | string | required | The search query |\n| `search_depth` | string | \"basic\" | \"basic\" for fast results, \"advanced\" for deeper analysis |\n| `include_answer` | boolean | false | Set true to get an AI-generated summary answer |\n| `max_results` | number | 5 | Max number of results (1-10) |\n| `include_raw_content` | boolean | false | Set true to include raw page content |\n| `include_domains` | string[] | [] | Only include results from these domains |\n| `exclude_domains` | string[] | [] | Exclude results from these domains |\n\n## Response Format\n\n```json\n{\n  \"answer\": \"AI-generated summary (if include_answer=true)\",\n  \"query\": \"original query\",\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"title\": \"Page title\",\n      \"url\": \"https://...\",\n      \"content\": \"Relevant snippet from the page\",\n      \"raw_content\": null,\n      \"score\": 0.95\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n## Search Depth Guide\n\n- **basic**: Fast, returns top results with snippets. Good for quick lookups, news, simple facts.\n- **advanced**: Deeper analysis, reads more pages. Good for research questions, comparisons, detailed topics. Costs more credits.\n\n## Examples\n\n### Quick search with AI answer\n```bash\ncurl -s -X POST 'https://api.tavily.com/search' \\\n  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \\\n  -d '{\n    \"api_key\": \"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\",\n    \"query\": \"latest developments in speech synthesis 2025\",\n    \"search_depth\": \"basic\",\n    \"include_answer\": true,\n    \"max_results\": 5\n  }'\n```\n\n### Deep research search\n```bash\ncurl -s -X POST 'https://api.tavily.com/search' \\\n  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \\\n  -d '{\n    \"api_key\": \"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\",\n    \"query\": \"flow matching vs diffusion models for audio generation comparison\",\n    \"search_depth\": \"advanced\",\n    \"include_answer\": true,\n    \"max_results\": 10\n  }'\n```\n\n### Domain-restricted search\n```bash\ncurl -s -X POST 'https://api.tavily.com/search' \\\n  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \\\n  -d '{\n    \"api_key\": \"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\",\n    \"query\": \"arxiv flow matching TTS\",\n    \"search_depth\": \"basic\",\n    \"include_answer\": true,\n    \"include_domains\": [\"arxiv.org\"],\n    \"max_results\": 5\n  }'\n```\n\n## Notes\n\n- Always use `curl -s` (silent mode) to avoid progress bar noise\n- Pipe through `jq` for pretty printing when needed: `| jq .`\n- The API key is embedded — no additional auth setup needed\n- Rate limits apply; prefer `basic` depth unless deeper analysis is needed\n\n\nARGUMENTS: ASVspoof5 SASV track SOTA 2025 leaderboard power fusion ECAPA2 WavLM AASIST top systems"}]}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "254cc905-eaf7-4880-97f4-861f7703553e", "uuid": "c4439169-d064-4c2f-b690-9db1158ca2c0", "timestamp": "2026-07-17T06:00:14.533Z", "isSynthetic": true}
{"type": "assistant", "message": {"id": "msg_1784268035848", "type": "message", "role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "tool_use", "id": "chatcmpl-tool-8664e478cc0d013b", "name": "Bash", "input": {"command": "curl -s -X POST 'https://api.tavily.com/search' -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{\"api_key\":\"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\",\"query\":\"ASVspoof5 SASV track SOTA 2025 leaderboard power fusion ECAPA2 WavLM AASIST top systems\",\"search_depth\":\"basic\",\"include_answer\":true,\"max_results\":5}' | jq -r '.answer, \"=== RESULTS ===\", (.results[] | \"\\(.title)\\n\\(.url)\\n\\(.content)\\n---\")' 2>&1 | head -120", "description": "Tavily search for ASVspoof5 SASV SOTA"}}], "model": "GLM-5.2-w4a8", "stop_reason": null, "stop_sequence": null, "usage": {"input_tokens": 0, "output_tokens": 0, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 0, "cache_read_input_tokens": 0}, "context_management": null}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "254cc905-eaf7-4880-97f4-861f7703553e", "uuid": "71833f19-fde1-4573-952e-3e2a47bdb809"}
{"type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": [{"tool_use_id": "chatcmpl-tool-8664e478cc0d013b", "type": "tool_result", "content": "ASVspoof 5 includes ECAPA-TDNN and WavLM for state-of-the-art results, with power fusion techniques leading on the SASV track. The dataset features adversarial attacks and deepfake detection challenges. Top systems use advanced fusion methods for optimal performance.\n=== RESULTS ===\nASVspoof 5: Crowdsourced Speech Data, Deepfakes, and Adversarial Attacks at Scale\nhttps://arxiv.org/html/2408.08739v1\n# ASVspoof 5: Crowdsourced Speech Data, Deepfakes, and Adversarial Attacks at Scale. ASVspoof 5 is the fifth edition in a series of challenges that promote the study of speech spoofing and deepfake attacks, and the design of detection solutions. Compared to previous challenges, the ASVspoof 5 database is built from crowdsourced data collected from a vastly greater number of speakers in diverse acoustic conditions. Attacks, also crowdsourced, are generated and tested using surrogate detection models, while adversarial attacks are incorporated for the first time. We describe the two challenge tracks, the new database, the evaluation metrics, baselines, and the evaluation platform, and present a summary of the results. ASVspoof 5 is the fifth edition in a series of previously-biennial challenges [1, 2, 3, 4] and has evolved in the track definition, the database and spoofing attacks, and the evaluation metrics. In addition to the use of new spoofing attacks implemented using the latest text-to-speech (TTS) synthesis and voice conversion (VC) algorithms, adversarial attacks are introduced for the first time and combined with spoofing attacks.\n---\nThe Automatic Speaker Verification Spoofing ...\nhttps://www.isca-archive.org/asvspoof_2024\nIntema system description for the ASVspoof5 Challenge: power weighted score fusion. Ali Aliyev, Alexander Kondratev · Enhancing spoofing\n---\nGitHub - asvspoof-challenge/asvspoof5 · GitHub\nhttps://github.com/asvspoof-challenge/asvspoof5\n## Navigation Menu. You signed in with another tab or window. You switched accounts on another tab or window. * Notifications  You must be signed in to change notification settings. # asvspoof-challenge/asvspoof5. ## Folders and files. | Name | Name | Last commit message | Last commit date |. | Latest commit   History57 Commits 57 Commits |. | Tool-score-fusion | Tool-score-fusion |  |  |. ## Repository files navigation. # Asvspoof5 Baselines. End-to-End DNN classifier. End-to-End graph attention-based classifier. ## Baseline SASV (track 2). Two baselines for SASV are available:. * SASV Fusion-based baseline from SASV 2022 challenge here. + Input file should be replaced with those of ASVspoof5. * Single integrated SASV baseline: here. + This is an adapted version of a work previously introduced in Interspeech 2023. Use the above link to access the `asvspoof5` branch. Tool-score-fusion: a reference tool to fuse ASV and CM scores for track 2. You can’t perform that action at this time.\n---\nASVspoof 5 Dataset Overview\nhttps://www.emergentmind.com/topics/asvspoof-5-dataset\n* It enables the development of countermeasure and ASV systems by addressing spoofing, deepfake, and adversarial audio attacks in realistic environments. ASVspoof 5 Dataset is a large-scale, crowdsourced resource developed for the fifth edition of the ASVspoof challenge, designed to drive research in the detection of spoofing, deepfake, and adversarial audio attacks against automatic speaker verification (ASV) systems. The corpus is accompanied by a suite of 32 attack algorithms, including legacy and contemporary text-to-speech (TTS), voice conversion (VC), and—for the first time—adversarial attacks engineered using surrogate detection models. The resource includes carefully defined speaker-disjoint partitions, auxiliary data for robust encoder development, and extensive evaluation protocols, making it a comprehensive testbed for anti-spoofing and spoofing-robust speaker verification systems (Wang et al., 13 Feb 2025, Wang et al., 2024). The ASVspoof 5 dataset incorporates a comprehensive spectrum of 32 attack algorithms, grouped into TTS, VC, and adversarial attacks (Wang et al., 13 Feb 2025, Wang et al., 2024).\n---\nASVspoof 5 Evaluation Plan\nhttps://www.asvspoof.org/file/ASVspoof5___Evaluation_Plan_Phase2.pdf\nTrack 1 Track 2 Task Stand-alone deepfake detection Spoofing-robust ASV Scenario Generic Telephony/VoIP Classes bonafide (real)*, spoof (deepfake) target*, nontarget, spoof Decisions ACCEPT, REJECT ACCEPT, REJECT Metrics minDCF (primary), actDCF, Cllr [9], EER min a-DCF [11] (primary), min t-DCF [12], t-EER [13] Required scores 1 (deepfake detection) 1 (SASV accept/reject) Optional scores — CM, ASV subsystem scores Table 3: Phase 2 protocol and meta data files Track File name Usage Training 1 / 2 ASVspoof5.train.metadata.txt Meta-data of training set utterances Development 1 / 2 ASVspoof5.dev.metadata.txt Meta-data of development set utterances 2 ASVspoof5.dev.trial.txt ASV protocol 2 ASVspoof5.dev.enroll.txt ASV target speaker enrollment data list Progress / 1 / 2 details in data package details in data package Evaluation • Track 1: The ASVspoof 5 training partition must be used for the training of spoofin-g/deepfake detection systems.\n---", "is_error": false}]}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "254cc905-eaf7-4880-97f4-861f7703553e", "uuid": "4882b415-0eb7-4b52-ba4a-2415975cd030", "timestamp": "2026-07-17T06:00:43.427Z", "tool_use_result": {"stdout": "ASVspoof 5 includes ECAPA-TDNN and WavLM for state-of-the-art results, with power fusion techniques leading on the SASV track. The dataset features adversarial attacks and deepfake detection challenges. Top systems use advanced fusion methods for optimal performance.\n=== RESULTS ===\nASVspoof 5: Crowdsourced Speech Data, Deepfakes, and Adversarial Attacks at Scale\nhttps://arxiv.org/html/2408.08739v1\n# ASVspoof 5: Crowdsourced Speech Data, Deepfakes, and Adversarial Attacks at Scale. ASVspoof 5 is the fifth edition in a series of challenges that promote the study of speech spoofing and deepfake attacks, and the design of detection solutions. Compared to previous challenges, the ASVspoof 5 database is built from crowdsourced data collected from a vastly greater number of speakers in diverse acoustic conditions. Attacks, also crowdsourced, are generated and tested using surrogate detection models, while adversarial attacks are incorporated for the first time. We describe the two challenge tracks, the new database, the evaluation metrics, baselines, and the evaluation platform, and present a summary of the results. ASVspoof 5 is the fifth edition in a series of previously-biennial challenges [1, 2, 3, 4] and has evolved in the track definition, the database and spoofing attacks, and the evaluation metrics. In addition to the use of new spoofing attacks implemented using the latest text-to-speech (TTS) synthesis and voice conversion (VC) algorithms, adversarial attacks are introduced for the first time and combined with spoofing attacks.\n---\nThe Automatic Speaker Verification Spoofing ...\nhttps://www.isca-archive.org/asvspoof_2024\nIntema system description for the ASVspoof5 Challenge: power weighted score fusion. Ali Aliyev, Alexander Kondratev · Enhancing spoofing\n---\nGitHub - asvspoof-challenge/asvspoof5 · GitHub\nhttps://github.com/asvspoof-challenge/asvspoof5\n## Navigation Menu. You signed in with another tab or window. You switched accounts on another tab or window. * Notifications  You must be signed in to change notification settings. # asvspoof-challenge/asvspoof5. ## Folders and files. | Name | Name | Last commit message | Last commit date |. | Latest commit   History57 Commits 57 Commits |. | Tool-score-fusion | Tool-score-fusion |  |  |. ## Repository files navigation. # Asvspoof5 Baselines. End-to-End DNN classifier. End-to-End graph attention-based classifier. ## Baseline SASV (track 2). Two baselines for SASV are available:. * SASV Fusion-based baseline from SASV 2022 challenge here. + Input file should be replaced with those of ASVspoof5. * Single integrated SASV baseline: here. + This is an adapted version of a work previously introduced in Interspeech 2023. Use the above link to access the `asvspoof5` branch. Tool-score-fusion: a reference tool to fuse ASV and CM scores for track 2. You can’t perform that action at this time.\n---\nASVspoof 5 Dataset Overview\nhttps://www.emergentmind.com/topics/asvspoof-5-dataset\n* It enables the development of countermeasure and ASV systems by addressing spoofing, deepfake, and adversarial audio attacks in realistic environments. ASVspoof 5 Dataset is a large-scale, crowdsourced resource developed for the fifth edition of the ASVspoof challenge, designed to drive research in the detection of spoofing, deepfake, and adversarial audio attacks against automatic speaker verification (ASV) systems. The corpus is accompanied by a suite of 32 attack algorithms, including legacy and contemporary text-to-speech (TTS), voice conversion (VC), and—for the first time—adversarial attacks engineered using surrogate detection models. The resource includes carefully defined speaker-disjoint partitions, auxiliary data for robust encoder development, and extensive evaluation protocols, making it a comprehensive testbed for anti-spoofing and spoofing-robust speaker verification systems (Wang et al., 13 Feb 2025, Wang et al., 2024). The ASVspoof 5 dataset incorporates a comprehensive spectrum of 32 attack algorithms, grouped into TTS, VC, and adversarial attacks (Wang et al., 13 Feb 2025, Wang et al., 2024).\n---\nASVspoof 5 Evaluation Plan\nhttps://www.asvspoof.org/file/ASVspoof5___Evaluation_Plan_Phase2.pdf\nTrack 1 Track 2 Task Stand-alone deepfake detection Spoofing-robust ASV Scenario Generic Telephony/VoIP Classes bonafide (real)*, spoof (deepfake) target*, nontarget, spoof Decisions ACCEPT, REJECT ACCEPT, REJECT Metrics minDCF (primary), actDCF, Cllr [9], EER min a-DCF [11] (primary), min t-DCF [12], t-EER [13] Required scores 1 (deepfake detection) 1 (SASV accept/reject) Optional scores — CM, ASV subsystem scores Table 3: Phase 2 protocol and meta data files Track File name Usage Training 1 / 2 ASVspoof5.train.metadata.txt Meta-data of training set utterances Development 1 / 2 ASVspoof5.dev.metadata.txt Meta-data of development set utterances 2 ASVspoof5.dev.trial.txt ASV protocol 2 ASVspoof5.dev.enroll.txt ASV target speaker enrollment data list Progress / 1 / 2 details in data package details in data package Evaluation • Track 1: The ASVspoof 5 training partition must be used for the training of spoofin-g/deepfake detection systems.\n---", "stderr": "", "interrupted": false, "isImage": false, "noOutputExpected": false}}
